name: George Restaurant & Bar

reviews.review_text: George Restaurant and Bar in Goa is a true gem! Established in 1956, it offers a fantastic blend of history and delicious food. I tried the beef, crab, chicken, and bun, and everything was exceptionally tasty. The flavors are authentic, and the service is warm. A must-visit for food lovers!

Went for an early dinner, on a weekday.
This restaurant is recommended for Goan cuisine.
We go there mainly for their meat preparations.
Starters:
Beef salted tongue, Pork cream chop, sausage pao (bread) - all good, & Bombay duck rava fried (v. mediocre).
Mains: Beef pulav (super, sharing portion).
Dessert: Caramel pudding. (no other Dessert on the menu!)
Except for the fish (Bombil),  the food was enjoyable.
Service good.
Ambiance somewhat noisy, as faces the busy road traffic.
They serve alcohol - no alcohol menu though,  for reasons best known to them.
Would recommend this place for a decent Goan meal, mainly for the meats.

I recently visited George restaurant and bar and I was utterly appalled by the experience. After a forgettable meal, nature called, and I politely asked to use the restroom. To my shock and disbelief, the staff refused. Yes, you read that correctly—denied access to a basic facility that any paying customer should be entitled to.

The excuse? “Only paying customers can use the restroom.” I had already ordered food and drinks, mind you, and was in the middle of eating. Not only was this policy incredibly bizarre, but it also felt downright disrespectful. There is absolutely no reason a customer should be treated like this, and it’s completely against the spirit of hospitality.

The staff was unhelpful and cold when I asked for clarification, and it left a really bad taste in my mouth—literally and figuratively. I will NEVER return to a place that doesn’t have the decency to provide basic customer service or common human decency. If you’re looking for a place that values basic courtesy and respect, look elsewhere.

description:
**George Restaurant & Bar: A Culinary Gem in Goa**  

Nestled in the bustling Complex Altinho, George Restaurant & Bar holds an impressive rating of 4.1 based on the feedback of nearly 1,100 patrons. This lively establishment offers its guests a taste of Goa through a menu that emphasizes succulent pork, delectable prawns, and an array of meat dishes, earning high praise for their authentic offerings while also serving inviting alcoholic beverages. Established in 1956, George Restaurant & Bar combines a rich history with a commitment to traditional Goan cuisine that draws visitors from far and wide.

**Ambiance & Design**  

From the moment you step into George Restaurant & Bar, the eclectic ambiance envelops you. The restaurant captures a casual charm characteristic of coastal eateries, adorned with vibrant colors and rustic wooden furniture. The warm lighting creates an inviting atmosphere, perfect for enjoying a leisurely meal or engaging conversation over drinks. However, some reviews note that the venue can become a bit noisy due to its location along a busy road, which may detract from a completely serene dining experience. The hustle and bustle outside seems to blend seamlessly with the lively vibe within, adding to the restaurant's charm.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**  

George Restaurant & Bar takes pride in its menu, which features signature dishes that highlight the best of Goan cuisine. The pork cream chop and the beef pulav have earned particular accolades for their robust flavors and generous portions, making them favorites among the many offerings. A customer mentioned enjoying the beef salted tongue and sausage pao as delightful starters, while others were keen on trying the Bombay duck rava fried, though opinions on it seem varied. For those with a sweet tooth, the caramel pudding stands out as a signature dessert, despite the limited options for sweets available on the menu. The restaurant's emphasis on meat dishes, particularly pork and beef, has won it a devoted following among meat lovers.

**Customer Experience & Service**  

While many guests rave about the friendly service at George Restaurant & Bar, it's important to note that experiences can vary. Most reviews commend the staff for their warmth and attentiveness, creating a hospitable environment that complements the culinary offerings. However, one unfortunate experience was detailed where a customer was denied access to the restroom, leading to a rather unsettling conclusion to their visit. This discrepancy in service serves as a reminder of the importance of consistent hospitality in the dining experience, and while most patrons leave satisfied, occasional lapses can color the impression one takes away.

**Popularity & Reviews**  

George Restaurant & Bar has accumulated a loyal fan base over the years, reflected in the steady stream of positive reviews and the frequent mentions on social media. Diners celebrate its delicious Goan cuisine, with many suggesting it as a must-visit for anyone looking to savor local flavors. Though the lack of an alcohol menu raises a few eyebrows among customers, the beverages serve as a complementary touch to the dining experience, even if the offerings aren't overtly showcased. 

**Utilizing Visual Content**  

Reviewers have provided a glimpse into their experiences with photos that showcase both the delicious presentations of the food and the restaurant's decor. Images reveal plated dishes that evoke cravings, from the beautifully arranged beef pulav to the appealing pork cream chop. The restaurant's cozy setup can also be appreciated through snapshots of the inviting dining area, making it clear why many consider this venue a comforting spot. 

In conclusion, George Restaurant & Bar is a treasured establishment in Goa, with roots that run deep in the local culinary landscape. With its focus on hearty, flavorful dishes and a warm atmosphere, it is undoubtedly a place where both locals and visitors can come together to enjoy the best of Goan cuisine. While there may be room for improvement in service consistency, its legacy and passionate fan base widely affirm its place in the hearts of food lovers.
